Swedish Finance Minister Anders Borg Quits Politics
STOCKHOLMâ€”Sweden's finance minister of eight years Anders Borg said he was leaving party politics a day after the center-right government lost parliamentary elections.
Mr. Borg has been a high-profile public figure alongside Prime Minister Fredrik Reinfeldt over two terms in government and had been seen as a possible candidate to replace Mr. Reinfeldt as leader of the center-right Moderate Party.